                        <persName role="scribe" corresp="PRS00000">Zä-Wäldä Maryam and four other scribes</persName>Five scribes were involved in the copying of the Ms. &#xD;
Zä-Wäldä Maryam copied the sections for Mäskäräm and Ṭǝqǝmt (quires I-VII); his name is written in the bottom margin of fols. 2r and 58vb. &#xD;
Bäʾǝdä Maryam copied the section for Ḫǝdar (quires VIII-X); his name is written in the bottom margin of fol. 59r (the same scribe possibly copied Ms. SM-003). &#xD;
Zä-Maryam copied the section for Taḫśaś (quires XI-XIV); his name is written in the bottom margin of fol. 87r. &#xD;
Tǝnsaʾe Krǝstos copied the section for Ṭǝrr (quires XV-XVII); his name is written in the bottom margin of fol. 120r.&#xD;
Täsfa Mikaʾel copied the sections for Ṭǝrr and Yäkkatit (quires XVIII-XXII); his name is written in the bottom margin of fols. 144r, 158r, 183vb.<date>18th cent. (?)</date>
                     </handNote>
